caption.p: Variation in the percentage of swabs tested ( y axis), when varying each parameter ( x axis). In each chart, the line shows the average over all instances generated with the given parameter value and the shaded area around the line is the 95% confidence interval. For parameters λ PP and λ TS, as they take categorical values, we show a box plot instead of a line plot. The central line indicates the median, the box spans the two central quartiles, while whiskers extend to the rest of the distribution (excluding outliers).
